In a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings) combine @basmati rice{1%cup}, @water{1 1/2%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low; cook until rice is tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick rounds. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine garlic, @cumin{1%tsp}, @paprika{1%tsp}, half the @za'atar spice{1%tbsp} (all for 4 servings), and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add spice mixture and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{10-15%seconds}.

> Watch carefully and stir constantly to prevent burning!

Whisk in @tomato paste{1}; cook, whisking, until slightly darkened, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Add @water{1 1/2%cups}, @chickpeas{1} and their liquid, zucchini, bell pepper, @veggie stock concentrate{3}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{}; stir to combine.

Increase heat to high, then cover and bring to a boil. Once boiling, uncover and reduce heat to medium. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until liquid has reduced and slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> For a thicker stew, mash half the chickpeas with the back of a #spoon{}!

Turn off heat; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Divide rice between shallow bowls and top with chickpea stew. Garnish with parsley and serve.